{"lemma":"حَبَراتٌ","slug":"حَبَراتٌ","root":"ح.ب.ر","root_slug":"ح-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6868","n6869","n6877","n6878","n6879","n6880","n6881"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a kind of well-cut variegated fabric"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"kind of broad shawl worn by women up to the feet"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"petechia"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6868","headword_ar":"حَبَرَهُ","root":"Hbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaborN","text_ar":"حَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hb~rhu","text_ar":"حبّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHobyrN","text_ar":"تَحْبيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K, TA;) or the latter has an intensive signification; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it beautiful, beautified it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adorned it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"embellished it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it plain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) namely, handwriting, and poetry, &c., (S, K, both in relation to the latter verb, and TA in relation to both verbs,) such as language, or speech, and science, (S, TA,) and pronunciation, and a recitation; meaning, with respect to the last, the voice [with which he recited]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habarahu","text_ar":"حَبَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, L, Msb, but in the Msb “ or, ” not “ also, ”) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaborN","text_ar":"حَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaborapN","text_ar":"حَبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHbrhu","text_ar":"احبرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and in an intensive sense ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hb~rhu","text_ar":"حبّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(God, A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, or an affair or event, S, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made him happy, joyful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glad;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affected him with a happiness, joy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gladness, that made his face to shine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabaAr","text_ar":"حَبَار"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avar","text_ar":"اَثَر"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appeared upon his countenance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xliii. 70, in explanation of the pass. form of the first of these verbs;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made him to enjoy a state of ease and plenty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"treated him with honour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth and S in explanation of the pass. form of the first verb as used in the Kur xxx. 14:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"treated him with extraordinary honour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xliii. 70, and TA.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hubira","text_ar":"حُبِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", properly signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was made happy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., may be used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, happy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sur~a","text_ar":"سُرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwrN","text_ar":"حُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and its syns. mentioned with it below, may be regarded as its inf. ns. Golius, app. from his finding"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabarN","text_ar":"حَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"explained in the KL as an inf. n. meaning The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being happy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAdo $udano","text_ar":"شَادْ شُدَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) assigns to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hubira jiloduhu","text_ar":"حُبِرَ جِلْدُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as on the authority of that lexicon, the meaning of “ hilaris lætusque fuit; ” but I have not found this verb in any Arabic work.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hubira jiloduhu","text_ar":"حُبِرَ جِلْدُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His skin was beaten so that there remained the mark of the beating."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habira AljuroHu","text_ar":"حَبِرَ الجُرْحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabarN","text_ar":"حَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wound broke out afresh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or became healed, but left scars."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, S, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habrato A^asonaAnuhu","text_ar":"حَبرَتْ اَسْنَانُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, * Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabarN","text_ar":"حَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His teeth became of a yellow colour mingled with the whiteness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became yellow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaliHato","text_ar":"قَلِحَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibirN","text_ar":"حِبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","TA","K","God","A"]},{"entry_id":"n6869","headword_ar":"حبّرهُ","root":"Hbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, in two places. ―         -b2-  Also, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHobiyrN","text_ar":"تَحْبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pared it well;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, an arrow. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n6877","headword_ar":"حَبْرَةٌ","root":"Hbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwrN","text_ar":"حُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Extraordinariness"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mubaAlagapN","text_ar":"مُبَالَغَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a thing that is described as beautiful."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [See 1.] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A musical performance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"concert, instrumental"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vocal"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"both,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaAEN","text_ar":"سَمَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in Paradise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, K;) agreeably with which signification Zj explains [the verb in] the verse of the Kur [xxx. 14, or xliii. 70]: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any sweet melody."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibirN","text_ar":"حِبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["TA"]},{"entry_id":"n6878","headword_ar":"حُبْرَةٌ","root":"Hbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibirN","text_ar":"حِبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n6879","headword_ar":"حَبَرَةٌ","root":"Hbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwrN","text_ar":"حُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A2-  and see also the next paragraph, in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n6880","headword_ar":"حِبَرَةٌ","root":"Hbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabarapN","text_ar":"حَبَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garment of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burod","text_ar":"بُرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burod","text_ar":"بُرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the fabric of El-Yemen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"striped"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munam~arN","text_ar":"مُنَمَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or this word, q. v., may perhaps signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spotted"},{"kind":"text","text":"]); (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of garment of the fabric of El-Yemen, of cotton"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"linen, striped"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxaT~aTN","text_ar":"مُخَطَّطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibarN","text_ar":"حِبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibaraAtN","text_ar":"حِبَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabarN","text_ar":"حَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabaraAtN","text_ar":"حَبَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [or rather ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibarN","text_ar":"حِبَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabarN","text_ar":"حَبَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"are coll. gen. ns.] Accord. to Lth, (Az, Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hbrp","text_ar":"حبرة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not a place, nor a known thing, but only signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa$oYN","text_ar":"وَشْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiborN","text_ar":"حِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Az, Mgh, Msb, TA;) and one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodN HibarapN","text_ar":"بُرْدٌ حِبَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwdN HibarapN","text_ar":"بُرُودٌ حِبَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burodu HibarapK","text_ar":"بُرْدُ حِبَرَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwdu HibarapK","text_ar":"بُرُودُ حِبَرَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, TA,) like as one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuwobu qiromizK","text_ar":"ثُوْبُ قِرْمِزٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrmz","text_ar":"قرمز"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying a certain dye. (Az, Msb, TA.) [The term ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabarapN","text_ar":"حَبَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is now applied in Egypt to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lady's outer covering of silk, black for the married,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white for the unmarried, worn in ridding and walking abroad; the former worn also by concubine slaves."},{"kind":"text","text":"See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabiyrN","text_ar":"حَبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","Az"]},{"entry_id":"n6881","headword_ar":"حِبِرَةٌ","root":"Hbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibirN","text_ar":"حِبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}